newsitem.title: USA: US spot jet dives lower with NYMEX, Gulf diffs up.
newsitem.headline: US spot jet dives lower with NYMEX, Gulf diffs up.

text.p: U.S. spot jet fuel prices slid lower Monday, led by the sharp drop in NYMEX heating oil prices, while U.S. Gulf (USG) differentials firmed slightly.
At New York Harbor (NYH), prompt 54-grade jet barrels were offered at 1.70 cents over the print, though no deals were confirmed there.
USG 54-grade nearby jet barrels changed hands at 2.75 cents under the NYMEX early in the day, with late day offers coming in at 2.70 cents under, up about 0.15 cent on the day.
USG prompt 55-grade barrels were offered at 1.85 cents under, up about 0.40 cent, though no trades occurred.
-- Matt Daily, New York Energy Desk +1 212 859 1626
